tps://imgur.com/gallery/nhJivZv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0PYvQvZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My wife of 5 years, who I have a 3 year old with, and I have had major issues due to her mental health for years. I’ve been so warn down by her drinking and anger that I’ve finally decided enough is enough. I had plans of asking her to separate and eventually divorce this weekend after yet another horrible week with her. I support the house fully while she decided to go back to school. I got a phone call yesterday from her crying her eyes out that her mother had finally not come back from another OD. there’s a ton of back story that I won’t get into but my wife’s child hood was an absolute nightmare due to her drug addict parents. Obviously this had caused her some major lasting damage. I’ve tried so hard to help and be supportive but there’s a limit to what a person can take. I finally hit that point and now this happens. I’m just tired. I feel thin. I have to be the supportive one because there really isn’t a choice. I can’t be the worst person in the world and leave her while this is going on. I can’t do that but now I’m left to make all the arrangements and cover the cost of whatever needs to be done which I don’t have the money to do. I have no idea how I’m going to get through this in one piece. I feel selfish and angry and sad. I’ve already been sucking it up for our sons sake and trying not to be an asshole to someone who walks all over me and treats everyone around her like garbage. I thought I was going to loose my mind before this shit. Don’t do drugs people. The effects are far reaching and extremely destructive. Sorry just venting to the void. Don’t really have anyone to talk to.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nhJivZv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[therobotmd101]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Nice murder cat</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bXjreua</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/V1O7T5m.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bXjreua</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[lotsofpicklesinmybelly]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Well this sucks</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/f0cgav6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TvWvjBk.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>After having a persistent cough for some time i went to my doctor who sent me to the hospital. After running multiple test the verdict is i have stage 4 hodgkin lymphoma.
The prospects for hodgkin aren't that bad, about 80% change of recovery.

Despite this i really doubt if i want to get treatment. I'm depressed af for so long and tired of this life but i also don't want to let down my parents. I think if i would die it will break them.

I'm so lost what decision i should make.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/f0cgav6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Crispy4Skin]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>That is a DAMN GOOD POINT!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/RHG4IKM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zukBndo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Link to tweet:

